title: Kate Middleton’s first state banquet: The Duchess of Cambridge wore Lotus Flower tiara
text:
Tweet 
Kate Middleton wore a Cartier Halo Tiara at her wedding in April 2011 and in 2013, at the annual diplomatic reception, the royal put on a Papyrus Tiara. 
This week on Tuesday, the Duchess of Cambridge, 33, shone in a Jenny Packham red gown accessorized with a Lotus Flower/Papyrus tiara at her first state banquet, hosted by Queen Elizabeth II, 89, at Buckingham Palace on the occasion of the visit of the President of China, Xi Jinping and his wife, Madame Peng Liyuan. 
The tiara chosen by Duchess Kate for this event was the same as the one worn in December 2013 at the Palace reception for diplomats. 
— British Royal News (@UKRoyalNews) October 20, 2015 Kate is listening to The Queen's speech #ChinaStateDinner pic.twitter.com/r77pF3VpBx
